<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 20 at 2:47PM MST  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Light Freezing Rain Possible Tonight...
A brief period of freezing rain will be possible the Helena Valley
late this evening through the early overnight period. Overall, if
freezing rain occurs, amounts look to be around a hundredth of an
inch or less. Although minimal, this could result in slick roads.
If you encounter slick roads, slow down and use caution.
Precipitation chances will diminish after 3 AM.</description>
